1576510587-Economic Update - Libertarian.title: Economic Update - Libertarianism Capitalism & Socialism
1576510587-Economic Update - Libertarian.description:
This episode of Economic Update features an exploration by Professor Wolff of how Libertarians defend capitalism by saying its many current flaws/faults flow from the state's economic interventions, not from the system itself. He then explains why Libertarians oppose socialism as another, even more, state-dominated intervention into the capitalistic system. Prof. Wolff then offers a critique of Libertarianism based on Capitalism's long history of strong state interventions and socialism's long-standing anarchistic components. He goes on to wrap it all up by inviting Libertarians and Socialists to find potential points of agreement against capitalism.

source: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d-sbFNk1mPw

1578079622-Tik Tok - Censorship coming f.title: Tik Tok: Censorship coming from India & US, not China
1578079622-Tik Tok - Censorship coming f.description:
TikTok has released its first "transparency report," saying that India led the number of requests for information (107) during the first half of 2019. The United States government made 79 requests, including some for content removal. According to the report, zero claims were made from China. Legal and media analyst Lionel, discusses what this says about censorship.
